               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Taz̲kirat al-awliyāʾ by ʿAṭṭār</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh87000556 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91002492" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1564x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Substantial fragment of a damaged, though high-quality manuscript comprising a later augmented recension of the famous collection of hagiographic biographies, the 
                <title key="work_21126">Taz̲kirat al-awliyāʾ</title>by 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100000000818.0x000215 viaf_120724759" role="aut">Shaykh Abū Ḥāmid Farīd al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Ibrāhīm Nayshāpūrī takhalluṣ ʿAṭṭār</persName>(d. circa 627/1230).
                        </p>
                        <p>This recension rearranges original entries with additional entries otherwise unknown in an order dissimilar to that found in the earliest reliable manuscript copies, ending abruptly at a point that can be conjectured to having lost approximately sixteen entries before the formal conclusion in complete manuscripts of the later augmented recension.</p>
                        <p>Defective, omitting the preface and first entry from the beginning, as well as a number of entries from the end.</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; datable to early-sixteenth-century Iran or India.</p>
                        <p>Gilt and polychrome rulings throughout; gilt rulings occasionally replaced with yellow pigment toward the end.</p>
                        <p>Corrections and dense annotations (ff. 186r, 248r, 248r-249r, for example); annotations erased ff. 153v-154r.</p>
                        <p>Rebound in IOL red half leather covers, stamp dated 13 Feb 1925.</p>
                        <p>Folios remounted on guards; cropped, prominently stained up to the lower half, wormholes, later repairs.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100000000818.0x000215 viaf_120724759">ʿAṭṭār</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_120724759">عطّار</persName>
                     </author>
